<sec id="id-087432a2-3632-4336-d8d2-2e8cece6ec86"><title><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="d33aeb56-cdc0-4584-ece6-cf3190a494e4" timestamp="1627509734223"?>Introduction<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="d33aeb56-cdc0-4584-ece6-cf3190a494e4"?></title><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="044b5664-fff6-466b-fea9-9790aef51f41" timestamp="1627509801526"?>A very significant aspect of the ISO/IEC 14662 “<italic>Information technology -Open-edi Reference Model/ Technologies de l’information – Modèle de reference EDI-ouvert</italic>”, is that it focuses on the making of commitments among autonomous parties as a whole. ISO/IEC 14662 is very important in that (1) it is transaction-based; and, (2) that these transactions pertain to and support the making of commitments among Persons. Further the Open-edi Reference Model addresses the totality of standardisation requirements in support of learning transaction, and acknowledges that these need to be viewed from two different but complementary perspectives.<xref ref-type="fn" as:rid="chunks/82851/id-168e6634-d1c9-4a8b-8dfe-44ca45929510.xml#id-25127392-47f2-4ae1-ed9d-9dbbdb4f6989" id="id-75adaa99-a45d-4f62-beb7-43a4a38084a9" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref><fn id="id-25127392-47f2-4ae1-ed9d-9dbbdb4f6989"><p>The ISO/IEC 14662 <italic>Open-edi Reference Model</italic> serves as the basis of the 2000 Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) between ISO, IEC, ITU and the UN/ECE on concerning standardization in the field of electronic business ( see&lt; <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://www.itu.int/ITU-T/e-business/files/mou.pdf" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">http://www.itu.int//ITU-T/e-business/files/mou.pdf</ext-link> &gt;</p></fn> The Open-edi Reference Model therefore makes a clear distinction between two perspectives; namely:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="044b5664-fff6-466b-fea9-9790aef51f41"?></p><list list-type="dash"><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="e2bdebbc-73ca-4e0f-ee96-8e32ad5edf6d" timestamp="1627509781856"?><list-item id="id-31319032-722a-4967-8b53-d7b9146b9ad2"><p>the Business Operational View (BOV); and,</p></list-item><list-item id="id-9b1c14c5-4ee1-410a-8d05-bd48ad392702"><p>the Functional Services View (FSV).</p></list-item><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="e2bdebbc-73ca-4e0f-ee96-8e32ad5edf6d"?></list><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="4b820fa6-bbfe-4efe-b30d-7646b01343c0" timestamp="1627525993398"?><xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-168e6634-d1c9-4a8b-8dfe-44ca45929510.xml#id-d9183803-1627-42fc-a63b-481e606634f1" ref-type="fig" id="id-43c1c283-100e-4671-9df4-77f2a60a95f2" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref>below is a copy of Figure E.1 in ISO/IEC 14662<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4b820fa6-bbfe-4efe-b30d-7646b01343c0"?></p><fig id="id-d9183803-1627-42fc-a63b-481e606634f1" specific-use="size:M"><caption><title><bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="dfc91f0a-7a02-4bf4-a69a-04d1328c9ff1" timestamp="1627525929725"?>Open-edi environment – Open-edi Reference Model<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="dfc91f0a-7a02-4bf4-a69a-04d1328c9ff1"?></bold></title></caption><graphic xlink:href="images/82851/E1" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/></fig><p/><p/></sec>
